** story ** 
Once upon a time, in a forest there lived a monkey who resided on a jamoon(berry) tree, which was on the banks of a
river. In the same forest there lived a crocodile and his wife. One day the crocodile came to the banks of the 
river and rested under the tree. The kindhearted monkey offered his some fruits. The crocodile came back the 
next day for more fruits, as he loved them. As days passed by, the crocodile and monkey became good friends. 
One day monkey sent some fruits for crocodile's wife. She ate the fruits and liked liked them but 
was jealous as her usband was spending more time with the monkey. She told her husband, "If the fruits are so juicy,
I would how sweet the monkey's heart would be. Get me the heart of monkey." The crocodile was not willing to 
kill his friend but he had no choice.